aiResponses.cover_letter:
I am excited to apply for the Customer Excellence Analyst role at Nu. As a Senior Software Engineer at TechCorp (2020–Present) and previously at StartupXYZ (2018–2020), I have built my career around solving customer-facing problems with data-driven engineering and cross-functional collaboration. At TechCorp I partnered closely with customer support and product teams to deliver features and tooling that improved customer satisfaction and reduced manual workload for support agents. For example, I led the development of an automated case-triage system (Node.js, AWS, PostgreSQL) that reduced first-response time by 30% and cut repetitive ticket routing by 45%, which directly improved SLA adherence and freed agents to focus on higher-value customer interactions.

My technical background (JavaScript/TypeScript, React, Node.js, Python, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes) gives me a unique advantage for this role: I can analyze customer interaction data, identify systemic issues, and implement scalable solutions that both improve operational metrics and the customer experience. At StartupXYZ I built monitoring and observability tooling that surfaced recurring issues in our payment flows; working with support and product, we resolved root causes and revised messaging to customers, which reduced related inquiries by a third. I enjoy translating quantitative insights into practical process and product changes, and I’m experienced with REST/GraphQL APIs and SQL to extract and analyze the data that drives better decisions.

I’m enthusiastic about Nu’s mission to fight complexity and empower people — it aligns with my approach to engineering and customer work: simplify processes, make information transparent, and create measurable impact. I bring strong collaboration skills from mentoring engineers and partnering with support, product, and operations teams, and I’m comfortable working non-standard hours and in shift rotations if required. I’d welcome the opportunity to contribute to Nu’s Customer Excellence team by combining technical problem-solving, process improvement, and a customer-obsessed mindset to build delight and trust at scale.
aiResponses.question_61004375: Yes — while my background is in engineering, I have direct experience collaborating with customer support and handling customer-facing escalations via email and chat. At TechCorp I regularly participated in incident communications and triage with support teams, drafted technical responses for complex customer issues, and helped implement automated responses and routing to improve throughput. I have experience analyzing support tickets, identifying recurring patterns, and delivering product and process improvements that reduced support volume and improved customer satisfaction.
